Common-facets.description:
Possible values for a filter, with an estimated total count if the filter is applied with one of the given values.

For example a list of facets for the `regions` filter can be:

```json
{
  "regions": {
    "prv-vlaams-brabant": {
      "name": {
        "nl": "Vlaams-Brabant",
        "fr": "Brabant Flamand",
        "en": "Flemish Brabant"
      },
      "count": 22,
      "children": {
        ... // a nested list of facets
      }
    },
    "prv-antwerpen": {
      "name": {
        "nl": "Antwerpen",
        "fr": "Anvers",
        "en": "Antwerp"
      },
      "count": 18,
      "children": {
        ... // a nested list of facets
      }
    },
    "prv-limburg": {
      "name": {
        "nl": "Limburg",
        "fr": "Limbourg",
        "en": "Limburg"
      },
      "count": 11,
      "children": {
        ... // a nested list of facets
      }
    }
  }
}
```

If the user then selects "Vlaams-Brabant (22)" to see the 22 results in Vlaams-Brabant, the `regions` filter should be applied with the value `prv-vlaams-brabant`.
